 on small\ndsDNA mechanics. But it is found to be ineffective to reproduce the\nsalt-dependent mechanical properties of DNTs. Also, unlike Martini, the time\nevolved PX DNA and DNT structures from the oxDNA models are comparable to the\nall-atom MD simulated structures. Our findings provide a route to study the\nmechanical properties of DNA nanostructures with increased time and length\nscales and has a remarkable implication in the context of DNA nanotechnology.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 31 Mar 2021 17:01:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-07-09"}
