$ are uninformative. From the combined ejecta mass estimate of\n$\\mathrm{^{22}Na}$ and its $\\beta^+$-decay, we infer a positron production rate\nof $<5.5 \\times 10^{42}\\,\\mathrm{e^+\\,s^{-1}}$, which would make at most 10% of\nthe total annihilation rate in the Milky Way.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 1 Apr 2021 09:36:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-06-30"}
