 in the limit of infinitely-strong between-group\ncompetition. When the group replication rate is maximized by an intermediate\nlevel of within-group cooperation, individual-level selection casts a long\nshadow on the dynamics of multilevel selection: no level of between-group\ncompetition can erase the effects of the individual incentive to defect. We\nfurther extend our model to study the case of multiple types of groups, showing\nhow the games that groups play can coevolve with the level of cooperation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 1 Apr 2021 10:54:57 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 11 Jan 2022 17:49:09 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 3 Feb 2022 04:14:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-02-04"}
